Hi, guys. When you use PyCharm with newest python (3.9) libraries, you can have issues with module cv2.
If you have this, here is solution:

1) In Settings --> Python Interpreter -> Install:
- you need to find modules: opencv-python and opencv-contrib-python
- Find option: specify version;
- choose version 4.5... (not 4.6, it is bugged);

2) When you want to use cv2 in code, just write from cv2 import cv2. Then you will be sure that every important function will work correctly;

